<a href="javascript:card_browser(149)">Orc Assassin</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(998)">Tower Assassin</a> x2<br>
Ulare Enquea<br>
The Balrog<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(321)">Under the Watching Eye</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(150)">Orc Bowmen</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(140)">Hate</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(167)">You Bring Great Evil</a> x2<br>
<br>
Shadow Card Total: 30<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> First off, You&#39;ll think: &quot;Well, he loozes to Discard decks,&quot; And, well, you&#39;d probably be right. But I use 60 cards anyways so I can get all the Free Peoples/Shadow stuff out real fast.<br>
<br>
And yeah, it&#39;s a ranger deck, I just need a Free Peoples side that can at least survive(and in worst case scenario, run.) so my shadow side can have some fun.<br>
<br>
Bid 1 so, if your opponent bids low, you can choose to go second.  Going second is fun because they hit your site 4, which rules, cuz nobody uses Gimli much these days. And, it&#39;s an exertion, which helps my shadow.<br>
<br>
Free Peoples:<br>
<br>
Free Peoples stuff is cheap enough so you can play it down and get it out of your hand fast. As to make room for all your really nifty shadow conditions! Two different Aragorns... just so you can decide on which one to get depending on who you&#39;re playing. Like ROTN for Moria and HttWC for Uruks, Nazgul, Sauron. Yey.  Always start with Arwen and Legoman even if you don&#39;t get a pony site one. 60 Cards is low enough that you&#39;ll get Aragorn/Boromir/Gandalf&#39;s Cart so you can dump your hand. Asfaloth is probably better on Legoman than Arwen now-a-days, since the Legoman with his bow and knives and Asfaloth lets you win skirmishes against decently strong minons, so you can finish off some big exausted minion somewhere. No Secret Sentinels, it was either those or PATHS or a 64 card deck.  I suppose 64 cards is a small enough number, but... it&#39;s 4 more than 60... End Free Peoples strategy. Highly original, I know.<br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
I originally made this shadow side back when this game was first created.  It took everyone out, except Gandalf, but it even took Gandalf out most of the time.  Then Rangers w/ Elves got Secret Sentinels and all sorts of nifty stuff to combat my cruely efficient shadow side.  So, it phased out until I tried it at the last tourney.  And people were taken off guard. So, to summ that up, if you like to watch people squirm as they decide who gets to die and live... and then nudge them in the right way with a little HATE... this deck is crying to you to play it.  I personally love this deck.<br>
But, being serious, This deck would probably lose a bit in a competative Tourney environment. Due to the popularity of Gandalf and Uruks. Which destroys your conditons and slows you to a crawl! :P<br>
<br>
on to strategy.<br>
<br>
Play UTWE and Orc Bowmen as early as possible. Play one, perhaps more orcs per turn to ensure you get your 4 archery and 4 exertions every opponent move. And then Hit you opponent with 5+ orce at Tol Brandir, some from hand and 3 from your discard pile, which either kills them in archery or overwhelms Frodo.  Hopefuly this will tear your opponent apart by itself, but, just in case, you have special cards that allow you get around some obstacles.<br>
Tower assassin, Kill elvses allies. Hate, Kill Gandalf. Enquea, Kill Gandalf or main companion.  You Bring Great Evil, Stop Aragorn or other exerting Archers, or Gandalf from healing.<br>
As you can See killing Gandalf is absolutely necssary for winning against a Gandalf deck. The Balrog usually helps get Gandalf into the &quot;Hate Kill Range&quot;(TM). And, don&#39;t play too many conditions against Gandalf... cuz if he takes them all out in one Sleep, He&#39;ll run all over you.<br>
<br>
Well, that&#39;s it.  First deck posted on this place, if you bother reading it... Tell me what you think.  And if you don&#39;t like me, Tell me that too. I&#39;m open to ideas ^_^<br>
<br>
